Sometimes someone asks me, &quot;But why didn't you choose race_x? Much better tank.&quot; Well, I didn't know anything about stats when I started, so I chose my race and class because it best suited my personality. <br>
<br>
What happens when I find out there was something I should have done? It's all part of the challenge I love, finding a way to accomplish it in spite of odds stacked against me. Maybe it's weird, but I <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> enjoy</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> obstacles. Stats, faction, etc., there is always something to consider. And something to be surmounted.<br>
<br>
Speaking of the Disease Cloud spell, despite the nerf, it's still  really not hard to &quot;taunt&quot; a mob with the combination of hatred-inducing spells we have. The main difficulty I have discovered is that it can be more difficult to maintain aggro for an entire fight; however, that is usually not necessary unless the only other people in the group are pure casters/rogue. In those situations when I need to keep aggro, the solution is to have me pull. <br>
<br>
